rare cause of death.

00:05:35.042 --> 00:05:39.153
In fact, only one
out of these 306 grandparents

00:05:39.177 --> 00:05:41.019
had died of TB,

00:05:41.043 --> 00:05:44.177
despite the fact
that in the early 20th century,

00:05:44.201 --> 00:05:49.021
TB caused up to 20 percent of deaths
in large Eastern European cities.

00:05:50.483 --> 00:05:53.158
Now on the one hand,
these results weren't surprising.

00:05:53.182 --> 00:05:54.912
People had already recognized

